---
description: "Model routing: directs GPT-family models to the gpt/ subfolder. Always active."
alwaysApply: true
---
You MUST choose exactly one subfolder before any reasoning: gpt/ or rich/.
Routing rules (in order):
1) If model family is GPT, select gpt/.
2) Else if user requests sparse or structured behavior, select gpt/.
3) Else select rich/.
After selecting a subfolder, you MUST immediately load 00-init and 01-router from that same subfolder.
You MUST NOT load any expert file before loading both files above.
You MUST NOT mix gpt/ and rich/ in one request unless the user explicitly overrides.
If subfolder cannot be determined, STOP and ask exactly one clarifying question.
